# System Cleanup Master - Windsurf Rules

project_type: python_cli_tool
framework: rich
target_os: macos

## Core Principles
- Safety-first approach: Always confirm before deletion
- Beautiful UI: Use Rich library for all terminal output
- User-friendly: Clear messages, progress indicators, emoji
- Well-documented: Code comments, README, visualizations

## Code Standards

### Python Style
language: python3.7+
style_guide: pep8
max_line_length: 100
string_quotes: double
indentation: 4_spaces
naming:
  - functions: snake_case
  - classes: PascalCase
  - constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE

### Imports
order:
  - standard_library
  - third_party (rich, click, psutil)
  - local_imports

### Type Hints
use_type_hints: true
example: |
  def get_size(self, path: Path) -> int:
      """Get size of file or directory in bytes"""

## Project Architecture

main_file: cleanup_master.py
entry_point: CleanupMaster.run()

classes:
  CleanupMaster:
    purpose: Main cleanup orchestrator
    key_methods:
      - scan_system: Detect clutter
      - clean_duplicates: Remove duplicate files
      - clean_caches: Clear cache directories
      - organize_downloads: Sort files by type
      - show_summary: Display results

## UI Guidelines

terminal_library: rich
colors:
  info: cyan
  success: green
  warning: yellow
  error: red
  processing: magenta

components:
  - Progress bars for long operations
  - Tables for data display
  - Panels for summaries
  - Confirm prompts before deletion
  - Emoji for visual appeal

example_output: |
  🧹 Cleaning caches...
  ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━ 100%
  ✓ Cleaned 12 caches (1.4GB freed)

## File Operations

path_library: pathlib
safety_checks:
  - Verify file exists before operations
  - Check permissions
  - Handle errors gracefully
  - Never delete without confirmation
  - Keep backups when appropriate

duplicate_strategy: keep_oldest_file
cache_threshold: 10MB
supported_extensions:
  documents: [.pdf, .doc, .docx, .txt, .xls, .xlsx]
  images: [.jpg, .jpeg, .png, .gif, .svg]
  videos: [.mp4, .avi, .mkv, .mov]
  archives: [.zip, .rar, .7z, .tar, .gz]
  code: [.py, .js, .html, .css, .java]

## Makefile Integration

prefer_makefile: true
common_commands:
  - make run: Interactive mode
  - make auto: Automatic cleanup
  - make status: Show disk usage
  - make clean-cache: Clean caches only
  - make organize: Sort Downloads

## Testing Strategy

test_approach:
  - Test with sample files first
  - Verify size calculations
  - Check permission handling
  - Test interruption recovery
  - Validate statistics

safety_tests:
  - Confirm prompts work
  - Verify no data loss
  - Check error messages
  - Test cancel operations

## Dependencies

required:
  - rich: ^13.0 (terminal UI)
  - click: ^8.0 (CLI framework)
  - psutil: ^5.9 (system utilities)

python_version: ">=3.7"
virtual_env: .venv

## Documentation Style

use_emoji: true
include_mermaid_diagrams: true
sections:
  - Overview with ASCII art
  - Feature list with emoji
  - Usage examples
  - Visual workflows
  - Troubleshooting

example_structure: |
  ## 🧹 Feature Name
  Description with emoji
  
  ```bash
  make command-name
  ```
  
  ```mermaid
  graph TD
    A --> B
  ```

## Performance Optimization

scanning:
  - Use parallel processing when safe
  - Cache size calculations
  - Lazy evaluation for large dirs
  - Stream large operations

memory:
  - Process files in chunks
  - Don't load entire files
  - Clean up temp data
  - Monitor memory usage

## macOS Specifics

cache_locations:
  - ~/Library/Caches
  - ~/Downloads
  - /tmp
  - /var/tmp

system_commands:
  - brew cleanup: Clean Homebrew
  - sudo operations: System-wide cleanup
  - security: Keychain integration

permissions:
  - Handle SIP restrictions
  - Request sudo only when needed
  - Respect sandboxing
  - Check access before operations

## Error Handling

strategy: fail_gracefully
logging: show_user_friendly_messages
recovery: continue_on_non_critical_errors

error_types:
  PermissionError: "❌ Permission denied. Try running with sudo?"
  FileNotFoundError: "⚠️  File not found, skipping..."
  OSError: "❌ System error occurred"

## Version Control

commit_style: conventional_commits
branch_strategy: feature_branches
pre_commit:
  - Run tests
  - Check formatting
  - Update docs

## AI Assistant Behavior

when_suggesting_code:
  - Show complete, working examples
  - Include error handling
  - Add helpful comments
  - Use existing patterns
  - Maintain UI consistency

when_helping_users:
  - Understand goal first
  - Suggest Makefile commands
  - Explain what happens
  - Show expected output
  - Provide alternatives

when_adding_features:
  - Update main class
  - Add Makefile target
  - Update documentation
  - Add visualizations
  - Write tests

## Common Patterns

progress_bar: |
  with Progress(console=self.console) as progress:
      task = progress.add_task("[cyan]Loading...", total=100)
      progress.advance(task)

confirmation: |
  if Confirm.ask("Continue?", default=True):
      # perform action

table_display: |
  table = Table(title="Results", box=box.ROUNDED)
  table.add_column("Item", style="cyan")
  table.add_column("Size", style="green")
  table.add_row("example", "1.5 GB")
  console.print(table)

